reviews.review_text: Great show One of the best shows of '92.

Best show of 92? most likely.... My friend and I are doing a 1990s vince-era analysis, where we go through every year and listen to the shows in order and pick out the best shows and the most unusual moments, good or bad. It's taken us years. We listen to every single show from 95, 94, 93, and now we're finishing up 92.

 There are not that many 5-star shows from 1992.    So far, 12/6 is up there, and back in June that first night they played Charlotte Coliseum is head and shoulders above the rest.

This show, and actually 12-13, and I've yet to listen to 12:17, but these shows are on the five-star consistency of the early part of 1993. So maybe it's not fair to really judge these December shows as being part of 92, they're more like ninety three shows really. But yeah this is a good one. If you like it when Phil's bass is deep n loud you'll like this one, although there is something a little out of whack with his overall bass tone, but yeah this is a good one.  This is one of those shows where you'll notice every band members, all six guys are just nailing all they're little Parts, every little fill during the verses and during the jams, Argent spot on, like they're clicking really well and just listening to each other and everyone having fun. Especially notice how great fences playing in throughout this show. He get such a bad rap and here he is a five-star classy piano player...
Tight show and sound Get this one it does not disappoint ! Extreme jams all over the place, First set , second set, take your pick, and the encore Casey Jones come on......
